## What is an accessor method?

An **accessor method** gives the value that is currently assigned to an instance variable.

For example, the `public`(#e7e8ea) **accessor method** `getTitle`(#e7e8ea) allows other classes to get the current value of the `private`(#e7e8ea) **instance variable** `title`(#e7e8ea).

```
public class Song {
  private String title;

  public String getTitle() {
    return title;
  }
}
```

The method is `public`(#e7e8ea) so it can be accessed from outside of the class. The return type is the same as the data type of the instance variable. The name of the method is typically `get`(#e7e8ea) followed by the name of the instance variable.
